Caribbean
---
Dominican Republic. 8 Jan 2016. (susp.) 3 cases: Localities affected: Boca Chica 2 cases, Santo Domingoi Este 1 case; Samples sent to the CDC laboratory in Puerto Rico for testing; The National Surveillance System has been activated.
http://www.7dias.com.do/portada/2016/01/08/i203232_autoridades-sanitarias-indagan-posibles-casos-zika-virus.html#.VpE3CBXhDIU [in Spanish]

[Maps of the Dominican Republic can be accessed at http://www.atozmapsdata.com/zoomify.asp?name=Country/Modern/Z_Domini_Pol2 and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3925377,6591. - Mod.TY]

Barbados. 9 Jan 2016. (susp.) 8 cases; Blood samples will be sent to the Caribbean Public Health Agency (CARPHA) in Trinidad and Tobago for confirmatory testing.

[No information is provided about travel histories of these suspected cases to countries where Zika virus is occurring currently, so it is not possible to know if these cases were imported or locally acquired. ProMED will be interested in knowing the results of the laboratory tests.

[A map showing the location of Barbados in the Caribbean can be accessed at http://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/namerica/caribb/bb.htm]

